abstract: Nervous Democrats who never thought Bernie Sanders had a chance of winning the 2020 presidential primary are now asking the party's big-dollar donors to open their wallets to stop the self-described democratic socialist.
snippet: Nervous Democrats who never thought Bernie Sanders had a chance of winning the 2020 presidential primary are now asking the party's big-dollar donors to open their wallets to stop the self-described democratic socialist.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Nervous Democrats who never thought Bernie Sanders had a chance of winning the 2020 presidential primary are now asking the party's big-dollar donors to open their wallets to stop the self-described democratic socialist.
headline_main: Can Bernie Be Stopped? Some Democratic Donors Are Trying
headline_print_headline: Can Bernie Be Stopped? Some Democratic Donors Are Trying

abstract: The credibility of porn star Stormy Daniels will be the central issue when Michael Avenatti goes on trial in April on charges that he cheated her of $300,000 from a book deal, his attorney said Tuesday.

abstract: The fast-moving coronavirus isn’t just confounding health officials. It’s also bedeviling policymakers and central bankers who are struggling to assess the economic damage from an outbreak that's reached 37 countries and territories, infected 80,000 people and killed 2,700 worldwide.

It’s also bedeviling policymakers and central bankers who are struggling to assess the economic damage from an outbreak that's reached 37 countries and territories, infected 80,000 people and killed 2,700 worldwide.
headline_main: Coronavirus Poses Tough Challenge for Economic Policymakers

abstract: A rebellion by GOP politicians in liberal Oregon intensified Tuesday when Republican members of the House joined their Senate counterparts in a walkout, freezing legislation on climate change, wildfire mitigation, homeless assistance and a landmark compromise between the timber industry and environmentalists.
snippet: A rebellion by GOP politicians in liberal Oregon intensified Tuesday when Republican members of the House joined their Senate counterparts in a walkout, freezing legislation on climate change, wildfire mitigation, homeless assistance and a landmar...
lead_paragraph: SALEM, Ore. — A rebellion by GOP politicians in liberal Oregon intensified Tuesday when Republican members of the House joined their Senate counterparts in a walkout, freezing legislation on climate change, wildfire mitigation, homeless assistance and a landmark compromise between the timber industry and environmentalists.
headline_main: Oregon Climate Battle: GOP Walkout Reveals Sharp Divisions
headline_print_headline: Oregon Climate Battle: GOP Walkout Reveals Sharp Divisions

abstract: Former Illinois Gov. Rod Blagojevich won his freedom last week when President Donald Trump commuted his prison sentence, but he may lose his law licence.
snippet: Former Illinois Gov. Rod Blagojevich won his freedom last week when President Donald Trump commuted his prison sentence, but he may lose his law licence.
lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — Former Illinois Gov. Rod Blagojevich won his freedom last week when President Donald Trump commuted his prison sentence, but he may lose his law licence.
headline_main: Illinois Lawyers Say Blagojevich Should Be Disbarred
headline_print_headline: Illinois Lawyers Say Blagojevich Should Be Disbarred

abstract: U.S. Senate Republicans on Tuesday reacted skeptically to the Trump administration's request to continue a controversial but inactive domestic surveillance program that collects data on U.S. phone calls and text messages.
snippet: U.S. Senate Republicans on Tuesday reacted skeptically to the Trump administration's request to continue a controversial but inactive domestic surveillance program that collects data on U.S. phone calls and text messages.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Senate Republicans on Tuesday reacted skeptically to the Trump administration's request to continue a controversial but inactive domestic surveillance program that collects data on U.S. phone calls and text messages.
headline_main: Republicans Look to Drop Domestic Spying on U.S. Phones, Texts
headline_print_headline: Republicans Look to Drop Domestic Spying on U.S. Phones, Texts

abstract: A federal judge on Tuesday brought in nearly all members of the jury that convicted Trump ally Roger Stone on charges related to the Russia investigation in order to answer questions on allegations of juror misconduct.
snippet: A federal judge on Tuesday brought in nearly all members of the jury that convicted Trump ally Roger Stone on charges related to the Russia investigation in order to answer questions on allegations of juror misconduct.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A federal judge on Tuesday brought in nearly all members of the jury that convicted Trump ally Roger Stone on charges related to the Russia investigation in order to answer questions on allegations of juror misconduct.
headline_main: Stone Judge Calls Back Jurors to Address Misconduct Claims
headline_print_headline: Stone Judge Calls Back Jurors to Address Misconduct Claims

abstract: A Connecticut opera singer is now mentally competent to stand trial on charges that she sped through a checkpoint outside President Donald Trump's Mar-a-Lago resort, drawing gunfire from law enforcement officers, her attorney says.
snippet: A Connecticut opera singer is now mentally competent to stand trial on charges that she sped through a checkpoint outside President Donald Trump's Mar-a-Lago resort, drawing gunfire from law enforcement officers, her attorney says.
lead_paragraph: WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. — A Connecticut opera singer is now mentally competent to stand trial on charges that she sped through a checkpoint outside President Donald Trump's Mar-a-Lago resort, drawing gunfire from law enforcement officers, her attorney says.
headline_main: Singer Who Drew Fire at Mar-a-Lago Competent to Face Trial
headline_print_headline: Singer Who Drew Fire at Mar-a-Lago Competent to Face Trial

abstract: Richard H. Clarida, the Federal Reserve vice chair, said the central bank was monitoring the virus, as worries roiled markets for a second day.
snippet: Richard H. Clarida, the Federal Reserve vice chair, said the central bank was monitoring the virus, as worries roiled markets for a second day.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Federal Reserve is watching developments surrounding the deadly coronavirus closely, but a top official on Tuesday signaled that the central bank is not yet ready to act.

snippet: Coronavirus, clashes in India, Kobe Bryant: Here’s what you need to know.
lead_paragraph: The top U.S. health official warned that the coronavirus outbreak, which has already sickened nearly 80,000 people in 37 countries, could hit the country hard, as chaos in the rest of the world drew attention to the need for a global game plan.
